<B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=5><P ALIGN="CENTER">Net Present Values Learning Plan 2</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER">Annuities</P>
</B></FONT><FONT FACE="Arial">
<P>While working through this plan you should be referring to your lecture notes titled ‘Net Present Values'.</P>

<B><P>Annuity</P>

</B><P>An annuity is an arrangement whereby a fixed sum is paid in exchange for regular amounts to be received at fixed intervals for a specified time.   Such schemes are usually offered by insurance companies and are particularly attractive to retired people.</P>

<P>Study the example on pages 4 and 5 of your notes.   Work through <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 3 5 f~?">3-5 section f</a>.   Try <a href="launch.htm#q0215">q0215</a>.</P>

<B><P>Perpetuity</P>

</B><P>A perpetuity is a special case of an annuity which never stops providing the income.  <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 3 5 h~?">3-5 section h</a> may be helpful.   Consider the example on page 6 of your notes.</P></FONT></BODY>
